headlines.description: — P.J Washington had 20 points and nine rebounds, Terry Rozier hit some big shots down the stretch and the Charlotte Hornets beat the Detroit Pistons 105-102 on Thursday night to get back to .500 for the first time since Jan. 13.
headlines.shortLinkText: Washington, Rozier help Hornets down Pistons 105-102

headlines.description: — Kyrie Irving scored 40 points to lead the Brooklyn Nets to a 121-109 victory over the Boston Celtics on Thursday night.
— Tony Snell hit a 3-pointer at the buzzer Thursday night and the Atlanta Hawks came back from a 15-point deficit in the final six minutes to beat the Toronto Raptors 121-120.
headlines.shortLinkText: Snell's 3-pointer at buzzer lifts Hawks over Raptors 121-120

headlines.description: — Jimmy Butler scored 27 points and added 11 assists, Kelly Olynyk scored 20 and the Miami Heat beat the Orlando Magic 111-103 on Thursday night to move over the .500 mark for the first time this season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Heat top Magic 111-103, get over .500 for 1st time this year

headlines.description: — Tobias Harris scored 24 points and the Philadelphia 76ers beat the Chicago Bulls 127-105 Thursday night even though they were missing stars Joel Embiid and Ben Simmons for contact tracing.
headlines.shortLinkText: Harris scores 24, 76ers beat Bulls 127-105 without 2 stars

events.name: New York Knicks at Milwaukee Bucks

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo followed up his MVP performance in the All-Star Game with his fifth triple-double of the season to help the Milwaukee Bucks trounce the New York Knicks 134-101 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo has triple-double, Bucks rip Knicks 134-101

events.name: Minnesota Timberwolves at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Jaylen Nowell hit six 3-pointers on his way to a career-best 28 points, top overall draft choice Anthony Edwards scored 27 points, and the Minnesota Timberwolves rallied from an early 16-point deficit to rout the New Orleans Pelicans 135-105 on...
headlines.shortLinkText: Nowell has career night, Timberwolves rout Pelicans 135-105

events.name: Dallas Mavericks at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 32 points and the Oklahoma City Thunder held on for a 116-108 victory Thursday night against a Dallas Mavericks team that rested Luka Doncic and Kristaps Porzingis.
headlines.shortLinkText: Thunder beat Mavs 116-108 as Doncic, Porzingis rest

events.name: Golden State Warriors at LA Clippers

headlines.description: — Kawhi Leonard scored 28 points in three quarters and the Los Angeles Clippers routed Golden State 130-104 on Thursday night, sending the Warriors to their season-worst fourth consecutive loss.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clippers snap 3-game skid with 130-104 rout of Warriors

events.name: Phoenix Suns at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: Devin Booker returned from the knee injury that kept him out of the All-Star Game to score 35 points and the Phoenix Suns beat the Portland Trail Blazers 127-121 on Thursday night for their fifth straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Devin Booker scores 35 points, Suns beat Blazers 127-121

headlines.description: — De’Aaron Fox had 30 points, nine assists and seven rebounds, and the Sacramento Kings sent the Houston Rockets to their 14th consecutive loss, 125-105 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Fox scores 30, Kings hand Rockets 14th straight loss 125-105
